===Etymology===
Arising in the [[King James Bible]], an approximate translation from {{der|en|grc|εἰς τοὺς αἰῶνας τῶν αἰώνων||to the aeons of the aeons}} and {{der|en|he|לעולם ועד||forever and until}}, as well as {{der|en|la|in saecula saeculorum}} and {{m|la|per omnia saecula saeculorum}} (themselves from the Greek).

